article.description: — Marcus Domask tossed in 23 points to guide Southern Illinois to a 63-60 victory over Valparaiso in Missouri Valley Conference play on Saturday night.
article.headline: Domask leads Southern Illinois over Valparaiso 63-60
article.linkText: Domask leads Southern Illinois over Valparaiso 63-60
article.story: VALPARAISO, Ind. -- — Marcus Domask tossed in 23 points to guide Southern Illinois to a 63-60 victory over Valparaiso in Missouri Valley Conference play on Saturday night. Domask hit 9 of 12 shots for the Salukis (9-5, 2-0) and added seven rebounds and six assists. Dalton Banks had 14 points, Lance Jones scored 11 and J.D. Muila snagged 10 rebounds. Kobe King had 18 points and nine rebounds to pace the Beacons (8-8, 1-3). Ben Krikke added 16 points.
